The Pentagon confirmed on Thursday night the military dropped America&#8217;s most powerful non-nuclear bomb on what the White House says were Isis targets. JOHANNESBURG - The US defence ministry claims the so called &quot;mother of all bombs&quot; has killed 36 Isis militants in Afghanistan. The Pentagon confirmed on Thursday night the military dropped America s most powerful non-nuclear bomb on what the White House says were Isis targets.The bombing marks the first time this type of weapon has been used in battles.White House spokesperson Sean Spicer says, We targeted a system of tunnels and caves that Islamic State fighters use to move around freely, making it easier for them to target US military advisors and Afghan forces in the area. For the first time ever the mother of all bombs was used by the US military in combat, CNN s Barbara Starr reports.The US air force special operations MC-130 via parachute.The Massive Ordnance Air Blast Bomb (MOAB) also known as the mother of all bombs is a 9,800kg bomb that explodes in the air.Its blast is supposed to destroy a target area that can spread over thousands of feet.There is still no clarity on whether civilians were killed.(Additional information by CNN)